THEY ARE living proof that MZANSI just never falls short of producing talent.Every now and then they mesmerise motorists with their amazing pantsula dancing skills.Tshepiso Sediti and Pogiso Mokae from Mohlakeng in Randfontein dance at the robots in Auckland Park to make ends meet and to nurture their talent. They say dancing comes naturally to them.They started dancing while they were still young and have been perfecting their skills ever since.The duo sees themselves as choreographers in the future, and inspiring young up and coming Pantsula dancers